Unprotected.Net is a library that gives access to private, protected, and internal members of objects. Its primary purpose is for unit-testing scenarios, but can be used in many other ways. It uses reflection to give access to otherwise hidden fields, properties, and methods.

Open the solution and take a look at the sample. Tests will be added eventually.

PrivateMemberExposer:
    The PrivateMemberExposer is an object that extends private members to expose them publicly.

